      • setLocation

        public void setLocation(String location)
        Here, instead of setting an instance variable directly, we tell the superclass to follow its standard procedure for setting a property. The superclass will call processProperty(String, String), which is where our instance variable will finally be set. This allows the framework to serialize and deserialize key-value pairs to and from the URL fragment identifier.
